<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TPa4">
<l>āḻi maḻaik kaṇṇā oṉṟu nī kai karavēl</l>
<l>āḻi uḷ pukku mukantu koṭārttēṟi</l>
<l>ūḻi mutalvaṉ uruvam pōl mey kaṟuttup</l>
<l>pāḻiy am tōḷuṭaip paṟpaṉāpaṉ kaiyil</l>
<l>āḻi pōl miṉṉi valampuri pōl niṉṟatirntu</l>
<l>tāḻātē cārṅka mutaitta cara maḻai pōl</l>
<l>vāḻa vulakiṉil peytiṭāy nāṅkaḷum</l>
<l>mārkaḻi nīrāṭa makiḻntēlōr empāvāy.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>O protector of the rains [resembling] the ocean!</l>
<l>Do not hide back anything!</l>
<l>Entering the ocean, drawing [its water], thundering, climbing up,</l>
<l>with the body growing dark like the hue of the Primordial Being,</l>
<l>emitting lightning like the discus and always resounding like the rightward curling conch</l>
<l rend="indent">[that are] in the hands of Padmanābha with wide, beautiful shoulders,</l>
<l>May you pour [rains] without delaying in [this] world,</l>
<l>like the showers of arrows discharged by Śārṅga,</l>
<l>so that [the world] lives and</l>
<l>so that we too [may] rejoicingly bathe for the Mārkaḻi [vow],</l>
<l>O our maidens, accept [and] consider [this] attentively!</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
